<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>3. O <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">original_b64</code> está sendo gerado?</strong>
No código que corrigimos, o <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">original_b64</code> só era gerado dentro do <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">if lat is not None</code> — esse bug foi corrigido, mas se você ainda está usando a versão antiga do view, imagens sem GPS não geram o resultado.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>4. O template correto está sendo usado?</strong>
O view usa <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">home.html</code> mas confirme que o Django está apontando para o arquivo certo no <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">TEMPLATES</code> do <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">settings.py</code>.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Cola aqui o que aparecer no terminal quando você fizer o upload que a gente resolve na hora.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
